Description of apterous male. Color as in apterous female. Body length 3.2–3.25 ; structure of head including antennae as in female, head length: 0.32–0.34 , head width: 0.71–0.74 , about 2.21 times head length, antennae about 0.49 times as long as body, lengths of antennal segments 1–4 : 0.41 , 0.33 , 0.34 , 0.5 ; pronotum medially with a constriction, posterior part slightly wider than anterior, pronotum length: 1.07–1.09 , pronotum width: 1.25–1.28 ; lengths of leg segments (femur, tibia, and tarsi): fore leg: 0.93 , 0.79 , and 0.36 ( 0.05 + 0.31 ), middle leg: 1.18 , 1.25 ,and 1.07 ( 0.31 + 0.36 + 0.4 ), hind leg: 1.3 , 1.53 , and 0.72 ( 0.07 + 0.29 + 0.36 ); grasping comb relatively long, about 0.37 times fore tibia length; abdomen pleurally and ventrally without special modification, mediotergites almost flat, connexiva slightly raised, weakly convergent, all mediotergites and laterotergites with long blackish hairs; segment 8 (Fig. 33 ) about 1.5 times as long as wide, with dorsal hind margin concave, pygophore and proctiger (
Fig. 38
) simple, paramere (
Fig. 41
) with relatively broad basal part and slightly wide distally twisted part, apically blunt; other characters as in apterous female.
